#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:5
msgid "Emscripten Test Suite"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:7
msgid ""
"Emscripten has a comprehensive test suite, which covers virtually all "
"Emscripten functionality. These tests are an excellent resource for "
"developers as they provide practical examples of most features, and are "
"known to pass on the ``main`` branch. In addition to correctness tests, "
"there are also benchmarks that you can run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:13
msgid ""
"This article explains how to run the test and benchmark suite, and provides "
"an overview of what tests are available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:17
msgid "Setting up"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:19
msgid ""
"To run the tests, you need an emscripten setup, as it will run ``emcc`` and "
"other commands. See the :ref:`developer's guide <developers-guide-setting-"
"up>` for how best to do that."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:24
msgid "Running tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:26
msgid ""
"Run the test suite runner (`test/runner <https://github.com/emscripten-core/"
"emscripten/blob/main/test/runner.py>`_) with ``--help`` to see the help "
"message:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:32
msgid ""
"The tests are divided into *modes*. You can run either an entire mode or an "
"individual test, or use wildcards to run some tests in some modes. For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:46
msgid ""
"The *core* test modes (defined at the bottom of `test/test_core.py <https://"
"github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/blob/main/test/test_core.py>`_) let "
"you run the tests in variety of different configurations and with different "
"optimization flags.  For example, wasm2js or wasm64.  There are also non-"
"core test suites, that run tests in more special manner (in particular, in "
"those tests it is not possible to say \"run the test with a different "
"optimization flag\" - that is what the core tests are for).  The non-core "
"test suites include"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:54
msgid "`other`: Non-core tests running in the shell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:55
msgid "`browser`: Tests that run in a browser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:56
msgid "`sockets`: Networking tests that run in a browser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:57
msgid ""
"`interactive`: Browser tests that are not fully automated, and require user "
"interaction (these should be automated eventually)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:58
msgid ""
"`sanity`: Tests for emscripten setting itself up. This modifies your `."
"emscripten` file temporarily."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/getting_started/test-suite.rst:59
msgid "`benchmark`: Runs benchmarks, measuring speed and code size."
msgstr ""

